ActOther Than Statutory Authority
SubjectCreation of Umliisle Indian Reserve No. 4 (British Columbia)
PrecisOrder setting apart 46.15 hectares (114.03 acres) of land, for the use and benefit of the NAZKO FIRST NATION, formely known as the NAZKO INDIAN BAND, as UMLIISLE INDIAN RESERVE No. 4, in British Columbia.
